text: Great ambience.  Good food. Nice and cool sheltered dining with big fans that has an outdoor feel.  10% NTUC member discount applies. Good selection of mid priced muslim friendly food: halal zichar and satay, to western food.  Loved the mutton and babat satay as well as the fried beef horfun.  Would not recommend the beef burger (not a 100% beef patty, but a frozen proceesed one); and the kampong fried rice (no zing).  Drinks-wise liked the teh halia tarik.

Good Food great place and nice people.
They have live music performance on some weekends.
Many varieties of food to choose from.
1. Chinese Seafood(recommended)
2. Burgers and steaks
3. Dim sum(good)
4. Steamboat
5. Traditional Malay cuisine.

All the stalls here are Halal and the food taste great. This place can sit 200 people and more.
